- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computing solutions of polynomial systems using polyhedral methods, which is a common topic in symbolic computation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method for sparse systems, which is related to algorithmic complexity. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as the paper uses polyhedral methods to exploit the structure of Newton polytopes, which is a common topic in computational geometry. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with computing solution sets of polynomial systems, which is relevant to control theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper uses combinatorial methods to enumerate factors contributing to a generalized permanent.
